WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:01.829
Hey, good morning family.

00:00:01.829 --> 00:00:03.080
Praise the Lord.

00:00:03.080 --> 00:00:04.955
Thank you for joining us.

00:00:04.955 --> 00:00:06.080
What a blessing!

00:00:06.410 --> 00:00:07.946
We have some things we're going to pray about.

00:00:07.946 --> 00:00:15.759
First off, I just want to tell you all thank you for all your support, for all the likes, the shares, the comments down below, and the emails.

00:00:16.199 --> 00:00:19.137
We've been praying for all the things you've been sending us.

00:00:20.199 --> 00:00:25.564
There's a lot of you that are going through a lot, and Diana and I truly pray for you.

00:00:25.564 --> 00:00:25.952
We love you.

00:00:26.727 --> 00:00:37.280
We agree by faith that God is meeting you at the point of your need; that everything that you're ever believing for, what you're asking for, all of it, God has it.

00:00:38.760 --> 00:00:42.640
I believe this is going to be a good year for you.

00:00:42.640 --> 00:00:45.614
2025 will be a year you thrive.

00:00:45.614 --> 00:00:50.217
A supernatural abundant supply is coming to you.

00:00:50.217 --> 00:00:59.070
We see right now the SEC saying that they want to drop the case against XRP in the days ahead.

00:00:59.070 --> 00:01:02.159
I saw an article, so we're praying.

00:01:02.159 --> 00:01:04.240
That's what we've been praying for.

00:01:04.240 --> 00:01:10.433
We've been praying for the wealth of the sinner laid up for the righteous and the wealth transfer.

00:01:10.433 --> 00:01:17.995
I believe the wealth transfer goes hand-in-hand with the great revival that's about to take place.

00:01:17.995 --> 00:01:23.685
We will see one of the greatest revivals this world has ever had.

00:01:25.110 --> 00:01:34.216
When I was driving down the road on Sunday, I looked over and I saw a Methodist church on a hill.

00:01:36.479 --> 00:01:40.146
Instantaneously, I started seeing in the spirit when I was praying.

00:01:40.431 --> 00:01:42.600
I saw a storm coming.

00:01:42.600 --> 00:01:51.704
I saw the doves flying down and doing that circular motion.

00:01:51.704 --> 00:01:57.600
Remember I told you all I saw the doves and they were coming out of this bright light when I was praying?

00:01:57.780 --> 00:02:07.620
Then all of a sudden they started twirling and then they exploded, but they went all over the four corners of the Earth, all around the world.

00:02:09.089 --> 00:02:11.160
They went to all the continents.

00:02:11.160 --> 00:02:22.919
I believe again I saw those doves circling and the Lord told me, 'Brandon, I want you to pray for Easter.

00:02:22.919 --> 00:02:32.874
I want you to intercede for Easter and what's about to take place, for a great manifestation of my presence is upon my people.

00:02:32.874 --> 00:02:36.160
' I've told you all, what's the tipping point?

00:02:36.160 --> 00:02:38.495
What is it that we're waiting for?

00:02:38.495 --> 00:02:43.810
What is it that's going to thrust this thing into full gear?

00:02:44.560 --> 00:02:47.053
That's what I've been interceding for, Diana and I both.

00:02:47.302 --> 00:02:49.011
We've been just stirring ourselves up.

00:02:50.670 --> 00:02:53.680
How do you stay to the point of being filled?

00:02:54.187 --> 00:03:00.915
I wanted to study Katherine Kuhlman because I was like, 'What was the secret?

00:03:00.915 --> 00:03:03.462
How did she walk in what she walked in?

00:03:03.462 --> 00:03:07.450
' Billy Burke is somebody that I follow a lot.

00:03:07.450 --> 00:03:12.220
I love Billy Burke, but he talks about being filled all the time.

00:03:12.220 --> 00:03:14.780
Does he pray a lot before his services?

00:03:20.080 --> 00:03:22.880
No, he stays filled all day long.

00:03:23.280 --> 00:03:25.959
I thought, 'How do you do that?

00:03:25.959 --> 00:03:27.852
' You practice His presence.

00:03:27.852 --> 00:03:29.639
Billy Burke practices His presence.

00:03:29.639 --> 00:03:37.420
He sent me this, by the way, which I thought was so awesome; he sent me this anointing oil that has frankincense in it.

00:03:38.440 --> 00:03:39.459
What a blessing.

00:03:39.799 --> 00:03:44.429
There's a lot of you all that have been going to his meetings in Pittsburgh.

00:03:45.420 --> 00:03:50.009
You all are so kind to bring up my name; you don't have to do that.

00:03:50.298 --> 00:03:53.644
It's such a blessing that you all would go and support him.

00:03:53.644 --> 00:03:56.312
I pray that you're getting richly blessed when you go.

00:03:57.672 --> 00:04:08.619
Every time I go to a Billy Burke meeting, it is a treasure going into his presence, just sitting there in the meetings.

00:04:09.069 --> 00:04:09.935
It's tremendous.

00:04:10.351 --> 00:04:12.653
It's life-changing, isn't it, baby?

00:04:12.653 --> 00:04:17.371
All you need is one second in His presence and you'll be forever changed.

00:04:17.954 --> 00:04:22.919
It's not that Billy Burke is—well, it's not all about Billy Burke, folks.

00:04:23.239 --> 00:04:28.580
Billy Burke is a carrier and he practices the presence just like every single one of us.

00:04:28.580 --> 00:04:32.600
God's not favoring Billy Burke any more than He'll do something with you.

00:04:32.600 --> 00:04:41.273
Billy Burke's just taken 50 years to cultivate something inside of his life, of being dedicated to sitting at Jesus's feet.

00:04:41.759 --> 00:04:44.533
If you do that, God will use you.

00:04:44.880 --> 00:04:45.800
That's why Diana and I are hungry.

00:04:48.600 --> 00:04:53.062
If you can go to where the water is at, you can have a drink.

00:04:53.062 --> 00:04:59.827
If you can get to where the water and the flow of the Holy Spirit's at, you can get a drink.

00:05:00.743 --> 00:05:15.860
But if you're going where it's dry, you have to stir yourself up like we were doing yesterday, praying for the dryness.

00:05:22.709 --> 00:05:31.613
I saw great dryness in Amarillo and all around the area, and the Lord said, 'I'm bringing a rain.

00:05:31.613 --> 00:05:36.124
I'm going to bring a fresh rain.

00:05:36.124 --> 00:05:48.189
' Then I saw the Body of Christ floating down the river, enjoying themselves as a family.

00:05:48.189 --> 00:06:02.900
That might be something people in the South do, go tubing, but there's a lot of memories made on the river.

00:06:02.900 --> 00:06:12.854
Getting in the river, getting in the flow of the Holy Ghost, and then fanning that flame—you don't walk away unchanged.

00:06:13.039 --> 00:06:25.440
You fan it and fan it and you walk away and you bring it home with you and you live there.

00:06:25.440 --> 00:06:29.411
It's not a place to visit.

00:06:29.411 --> 00:06:33.590
Don't dry out once you get there.

00:06:46.127 --> 00:06:46.259
Don't let it die.

00:06:46.259 --> 00:06:48.280
It takes us doing it because here we are.

00:06:48.280 --> 00:07:01.334
We went to his meeting and we're so excited, but then you get away from it and you ask, 'How do you keep that fire going?

00:07:01.334 --> 00:07:13.404
' You've got that fire going inside of you and you're excited and radical, but then you have your day-to-day life.

00:07:14.736 --> 00:07:26.630
You go back to eBay, Poshmark, listing things, going to thrift stores, pressing through life, getting kids through school.

00:07:42.702 --> 00:07:43.017
All the things of life try to put that out because you're always leaking out.

00:07:43.017 --> 00:07:50.740
The lady at the grocery store was rude to you, maybe somebody at church was rude to you.

00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:07.520
The devil comes to try to distract you and try to make you upset.

00:08:07.520 --> 00:08:16.200
They always say if the devil can't get you, he'll keep you busy.

00:08:16.200 --> 00:08:27.880
That's exactly what he does; he tries to keep you chasing your tail.

00:08:27.880 --> 00:08:41.181
If he can keep you that way, then you'll go through your day and wonder what you did today.

00:08:46.240 --> 00:08:47.529
You didn't take the time sitting at His feet.

00:08:48.937 --> 00:08:59.383
The Lord spoke to me the other day and he said, 'The lengths that I require are not old, tired days.

00:09:08.382 --> 00:09:10.620
The lengths that I require are the new, fresh days out of the new wineskin.

00:09:10.620 --> 00:09:21.380
' Not giving Him the last, but giving Him the first.

00:09:21.380 --> 00:09:39.240
Giving Him priority, fanning the flame, and putting Him first—those are all ways you practice His presence.

00:09:39.240 --> 00:09:43.120
Not giving Him leftovers.

00:09:43.120 --> 00:10:12.604
'God, I'm tired, but I'll give you a couple of minutes before I go to bed,' which is better than nothing, but it's about making Him first place in your life and saying, 'Father, I need you today.

00:10:12.604 --> 00:10:21.013
When my feet hit the ground, God, I need you today.

00:10:21.013 --> 00:10:25.365
' Even when Billy Burke was talking about saying, 'I just need you.

00:10:27.555 --> 00:10:31.034
I need you today in this life.

00:10:31.034 --> 00:10:33.515
Holy Spirit, fill me.

00:10:33.515 --> 00:10:43.142
I need a fresh drink of your living water today.

00:10:50.690 --> 00:10:51.095
I'm desperate for you.

00:10:51.095 --> 00:10:53.120
Fill me.

00:10:53.120 --> 00:10:57.630
' The more you practice His presence...

00:10:59.980 --> 00:11:02.085
I want to sit outside.

00:11:03.413 --> 00:11:06.240
I like to see nature.

00:11:10.055 --> 00:11:20.783
I love the beauty of nature and I see Him in it.

00:11:20.783 --> 00:11:28.960
People say, 'Well, you know, evolution and all this stuff.

00:11:28.960 --> 00:11:46.253
' I think, how in the world could you believe in evolution if you sit outside for ten minutes and just look at the stuff that God created?

00:11:46.253 --> 00:12:00.440
There's no way that a tree went from an oak tree to a pine tree to a sycamore tree.

00:12:15.175 --> 00:12:15.460
I can't even fathom that.

00:12:15.460 --> 00:12:30.228
We have two eagles that fly around our house, and it's amazing how majestic an eagle is.

00:12:30.228 --> 00:12:31.970
Diana found this...

00:12:35.540 --> 00:12:52.780
I was thinking about all the trials that we face as believers and we get discouraged when we don't see the full manifestation of what we're going through.

00:13:01.392 --> 00:13:04.290
You get to that point of desperation, and I see it in so many of your letters.

00:13:09.390 --> 00:13:19.152
Whenever you get frustrated and you get weary in well-doing and you get annoyed at your circumstance, you have a tendency to start blaming God.

00:13:19.152 --> 00:13:24.103
'Why am I still living this?

00:13:24.103 --> 00:13:35.489
' We hear so much in things past that you didn't have enough faith to be healed.

00:13:35.489 --> 00:13:44.669
I can't tell you how many times I've been told that about Megan.

00:13:44.669 --> 00:13:58.939
People say, 'Well, there's a devil; it's because you opened the door through sin, brother.

00:14:03.581 --> 00:14:09.154
I believe there must have been sin in your life for this to have happened.

00:14:09.154 --> 00:14:23.959
' I'm telling you, you want to deck them in the face when they go off like that.

00:14:24.817 --> 00:14:37.503
I'm just being real because there's been people that just try to figure it out.

00:14:42.406 --> 00:14:45.034
I love when Billy Burke said this.

00:14:45.034 --> 00:14:52.756
He asked Katherine Kuhlman a question and she said, 'I don't know.

00:14:52.756 --> 00:15:05.106
' She told Billy, 'Learn three words, Billy, and this will help you all the way through your ministry: I don't know.

00:15:05.106 --> 00:15:16.491
' I don't know why you go through some of the stuff you're going through.

00:15:19.347 --> 00:15:22.866
I don't know why you're not healed yet.

00:15:27.324 --> 00:15:32.342
I don't know why you're still believing for it, like I'm still believing for mine year after year.

00:15:45.309 --> 00:15:45.766
You go through healing line after healing line and you're still believing for the manifestation.

00:15:45.766 --> 00:16:01.817
You get weary after a while and you say to yourself, 'God, are you there?

00:16:01.817 --> 00:16:05.715
' Was it a lack of faith?

00:16:05.715 --> 00:16:10.639
Did you not have enough heart after God?

00:16:27.315 --> 00:16:27.671
Did you not confess enough?

00:16:39.960 --> 00:16:40.240
You walk away defeated, feeling like you don't have what it takes.

00:16:40.240 --> 00:16:44.384
Am I the only one that ever walks away with that?

00:16:52.720 --> 00:17:02.151
You walk away feeling, 'I just don't measure up because I didn't quote enough scripture, obviously, because I'm still getting over this and the doctor's giving me this report.

00:17:02.151 --> 00:17:10.756
' So I walk away saying, 'Why do I even try?

00:17:10.756 --> 00:17:38.150
' There is a story in the Bible where Jesus told the disciples, when they asked if it was because this family was in sin that this happened, Jesus said, 'No, it was so that the glory of God would be made known.

00:17:38.150 --> 00:17:42.903
' It wasn't that they sinned.

00:17:44.452 --> 00:17:48.713
It wasn't that the blind child was under judgment.

00:17:48.713 --> 00:18:03.265
It was at that moment that the glory of God would be known.

00:18:10.370 --> 00:18:19.863
So it's not always a sin door, or he would have said it to the disciples then.

00:18:19.863 --> 00:18:32.655
Jesus never said her daddy was committing adultery or he was out smoking or drinking.

00:18:32.655 --> 00:18:49.686
He said it was that at that moment the glory of God would be made known.

00:19:16.108 --> 00:19:16.472
I had to take that for me because I've gone to all the healing services, one after another, countless times.

00:19:16.472 --> 00:19:37.160
Fall out in the spirit, get up, and believe 'today's my day,' and you walk away feeling defeated when people say maybe you didn't have enough faith.

00:19:41.000 --> 00:19:55.279
I know it's easy to get weary in well-doing, but I always go back to the scripture: 'When there is nothing else to do, stand.

00:19:55.279 --> 00:19:56.999
Stand therefore.

00:19:56.999 --> 00:20:06.405
' I will stand regardless of the circumstance of what I see.

00:20:06.405 --> 00:20:27.008
I'm not moved by what I see; I'm not moved by what I feel; I'm moved by what the Word of God says.

00:20:27.008 --> 00:20:36.819
Diana found this little bit of a passage that Katherine Kuhlman said right here.

00:20:55.227 --> 00:21:04.583
I feel it's necessary for some of you to hear this because I see you at the point of desperation, and you don't see your miracle, and you're weary in well-doing.

00:21:04.583 --> 00:21:08.533
Diana and I live it too.

00:21:08.533 --> 00:21:15.119
You have people look at you with that 'holier-than-thou' outlook.

00:21:23.720 --> 00:21:27.520
I was one of them.

00:21:27.520 --> 00:21:52.580
I looked across the table at a lady named Jane who was overcoming cancer, and I said, 'It's a mockery of the blood of Jesus for what He did on the cross for you to remain sick.

00:21:52.580 --> 00:21:56.159
' I crushed that woman.

00:21:56.159 --> 00:22:18.199
Out of trying to be so bold about my faith, basically what I was saying was she must not have enough faith.

00:22:18.199 --> 00:22:22.880
I was in my early 20s and immature.

00:22:22.880 --> 00:22:27.890
I'll never forget how I crushed that woman.

00:22:27.890 --> 00:22:43.719
When Megan got diagnosed three or four years later, I walked in her office and told her, 'I owe you a big apology.

00:22:43.719 --> 00:22:49.860
I'm at the bottom of the hole.

00:22:49.860 --> 00:23:07.507
' I've had people tell us all the time, 'Your daughter has devils; you need to go get them cast out.

00:23:07.507 --> 00:23:29.764
' We went to deliverance services and all kinds of things, trying to find a solution to autism.

00:23:32.909 --> 00:23:33.177
That's why I have compassion.

00:23:33.177 --> 00:23:39.291
Until you live it, you don't know.

00:23:39.291 --> 00:23:59.810
When I hear some of the things you're going through, I go, 'Brandon, shut up' compared to the pain some of you are going through.

00:23:59.810 --> 00:24:10.271
How can you complain when somebody else has it so much worse?

00:24:13.880 --> 00:24:14.640
But we have compassion for those that are hurting.

00:24:15.909 --> 00:24:16.120
You are warriors.

00:24:16.120 --> 00:24:17.079
Jesus is so proud of you.

00:24:26.148 --> 00:24:30.783
I believe with all my heart there's an expiration date to your circumstance, just like ours.

00:24:30.783 --> 00:24:34.600
Hope—that's what we do.

00:24:38.898 --> 00:24:49.840
We always put ourselves in hope and say, 'God, we know that you will meet us at the point of our need.

00:24:49.840 --> 00:25:06.440
' We don't know when that day of full manifestation is coming, but I believe in being fully persuaded that what God has promised, He is able also to perform.

00:25:06.440 --> 00:25:19.088
Even in the deadness of Sarah's womb and Abraham's old age, they believed in hope.

00:25:19.088 --> 00:25:28.320
Faith as a grain of a mustard seed, the Bible says, will move your mountain.

00:25:31.227 --> 00:25:31.520
I doubt my doubt.

00:25:31.520 --> 00:25:40.771
Devil, I refuse to let this doubt build a root inside of me.

00:25:40.771 --> 00:25:50.410
Out of the abundance of my heart, the mouth will speak.

00:25:52.659 --> 00:26:02.039
I renew my mind to what the Lord said I could have.

00:26:09.733 --> 00:26:11.748
I want you to hear this story about Katherine Kuhlman real quick.

00:26:11.748 --> 00:26:28.270
In the early days of her ministry, Katherine was greatly disturbed over many things that she observed in the field of divine healing.

00:26:28.270 --> 00:26:32.820
'I hated traditional tent healing services,' she explained.

00:26:32.820 --> 00:26:44.500
'Those long healing lines, the filling out of cards—it was an insult to your intelligence.

00:26:44.500 --> 00:26:54.856
' Once, after visiting such a service, she cried all night.

00:26:54.856 --> 00:27:05.265
She determined that with the Holy Spirit's help, her ministry would not be that way.

00:27:05.265 --> 00:27:12.987
She delved even harder into the word of God for answers.

00:27:12.987 --> 00:27:41.380
Katherine said, 'Too often I had seen pathetically sick people dragging their tired, weakened bodies home from a healing service, having been told that they were not healed simply because of their own lack of faith.

00:27:41.380 --> 00:28:11.006
' Her heart ached for these people as she knew how they struggled day after day, trying desperately to obtain more faith, trying to analyze their deficiency.

00:28:11.006 --> 00:28:19.960
They were unwittingly looking at themselves rather than to God.

00:28:19.960 --> 00:28:32.194
She saw the harm that was being done in attributing everything to lack of faith on the part of the individual.

00:28:32.194 --> 00:28:47.840
Kuhlman suggested that her prayer was answered in the spring of 1947 when she began studying the Holy Spirit.

00:28:47.840 --> 00:29:11.843
She realized that when the crucified Christ said, 'It is finished,' He included not only the salvation of the soul but the healing and deliverance of the body as well.

00:29:11.843 --> 00:29:27.679
Even if she never saw a single healing miracle, it would not change God's word.

00:29:42.848 --> 00:29:46.794
The secret of the power of healing is found in the person of the Holy Spirit.

00:29:46.794 --> 00:30:00.749
Katherine Kuhlman said a reporter once asked, 'How much time do you spend preparing for a miracle service?

00:30:00.749 --> 00:30:10.360
' She said, 'I stay prepared 24 hours a day.

00:30:10.360 --> 00:30:22.280
' She was frustrated seeing people walk away without their miracle.

00:30:22.280 --> 00:30:26.159
Hope deferred makes the heart sick.

00:30:26.159 --> 00:30:27.931
You're not alone.

00:30:27.931 --> 00:30:42.853
I know you've used a lot of scripture, prayed a lot, and fasted, but I believe there's an expiration date to your circumstance.

00:30:42.853 --> 00:30:50.782
Even if people die, they get their miracle on the other side.

00:30:50.782 --> 00:30:56.290
God's not a failure, and you're not a failure.

00:31:10.817 --> 00:31:11.062
You still have victory regardless if you get it on this side or the other side.

00:31:19.306 --> 00:31:19.559
I just choose to stay in a place of victory.

00:31:19.559 --> 00:31:24.560
I'm not going to let my mind wander.

00:31:24.560 --> 00:31:39.725
When days like that happen, put on worship music and rejoice like it's already happened.

00:31:39.725 --> 00:31:48.508
If the devil can't steal your joy, he can't steal your goods.

00:31:53.479 --> 00:31:58.568
The Bible says He gives a garment of praise for a spirit of heaviness.

00:31:59.182 --> 00:32:04.120
I just want to encourage you because I don't want to be hyperspiritual.

00:32:04.120 --> 00:32:11.782
I don't want to be the Hollywood Christian where everything is okay.

00:32:11.782 --> 00:32:14.898
I've got my stuff.

00:32:14.898 --> 00:32:26.700
Everybody has something they're going through, regardless of how much they try to make themselves look spiritual.

00:32:26.700 --> 00:32:33.714
No matter how big the name is, they've all got issues.

00:32:33.714 --> 00:32:40.193
They put their pants on just like I do.

00:32:40.193 --> 00:33:05.205
My relationship with God was birthed out of desperation and pure hell—not being able to read or write, being bullied as a kid and as a janitor.

00:33:05.205 --> 00:33:09.553
Hearing Him was out of desperation.

00:33:09.553 --> 00:33:16.773
That's why I say, how bad do you want it?

00:33:16.773 --> 00:33:23.679
Every single thing has not ever come to me easy.

00:33:23.679 --> 00:33:43.213
There's been things where I've seen greater victory than others, but it has come out of just being a bulldog on a bone.

00:33:52.287 --> 00:33:52.535
I refuse to give up.

00:33:52.535 --> 00:33:57.542
I'll seek Him and I'll find Him.

00:34:00.479 --> 00:34:11.919
I will touch the hem of His garment because if I have nothing else, I have Him.

00:34:11.919 --> 00:34:18.140
I've had eight visitations from the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:34:18.140 --> 00:34:24.280
Does it make me any more special than you?

00:34:24.280 --> 00:34:25.583
No.

00:34:25.583 --> 00:34:30.264
I seek Him and I find Him.

00:34:30.264 --> 00:34:31.676
There's no shortcuts.

00:34:31.676 --> 00:34:37.960
I continually feed my faith because I'm desperate.

00:34:53.364 --> 00:34:53.706
I want that little girl to get better.

00:34:56.480 --> 00:34:56.960
I want my family restored.

00:34:56.960 --> 00:35:11.000
I want the tangible presence of God on my life so that when I walk into an atmosphere, it changes.

00:35:11.000 --> 00:35:18.599
Not to give me glory, but to give Him glory.

00:35:18.599 --> 00:35:41.169
Bottom line is, if we get this glorious gospel preached throughout the whole world, then the end will come and all the drama of this world is over.

00:35:41.169 --> 00:35:46.387
All this other stuff doesn't matter.

